Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and Bola Tinubu of the All Progressives Congress (APC) took their presidential campaigns to south-east and south-south, respectively, on Tuesday. The PDP had its rally at the Stephen Keshi Stadium in Asaba, Delta state, while the APC held its own at the Umuahia township stadium in Abia. While Abubakar had Ifeanyi Okowa, his running mate, by his side, Tinubu was accompanied by Hope Uzodimma, governor of Imo. ATIKU IN ASABA          TINUBU IN ABIA       